text: Septoplasty with partial inferior middle turbinectomy with KTP laser
context: Septoplasty with partial inferior middle turbinectomy with KTP laser, sinus endoscopy with maxillary antrostomies, removal of tissue, with septoplasty and partial ethmoidectomy bilaterally.   (Medical Transcription Sample Report)

text: Chronic sinusitis with deviated nasal septum and nasal obstruction and hypertrophied turbinates.
context:
Operative Diagnoses

Chronic sinusitis with deviated nasal septum and nasal obstruction and hypertrophied turbinates.
after adequate anesthesia via endotracheal intubation, the nose was prepped with Afrin nasal spray.
After this was done, 1% Xylocaine with 100,000 epinephrine was infiltrated in both sides of the septum and the mucoperichondrium.
After this, the sinus endoscope at 25-degrees was then used to examine the nasal cavity in the left nasal cavity and staying lateral to the middle turbinate.
The 45-degree forceps was then used to open the maxillary sinus ostium.
This was enlarged with backbiting rongeur
There was noted to have prominence in the anterior ethmoidal area.
This was then opened with 45-degree forceps.
This mucosa was then removed from the anterior area.
he maxillary sinus ostium was then opened with 45-degree forceps. Tissue was removed from this area.

text: This was sent as right maxillary mucosa
context: Tissue was removed from this area. This was sent as right maxillary mucosa.
After this, the backbiting rongeur was then used to open up the ostium and enlarge the ostium on the right maxillary sinus.

Protecting the eyes with wet gauze and using KTP laser at 10 watts, the sinus endoscope was used for observation and the submucosal resection was done of both inferior turbinates as well as anterior portion of the middle turbinates bilaterally.
fter this was completed, a septoplasty was performed.
The flap was then elevated, overlying the spur that was protruding into the right nasal cavity. This was excised with a #15 blade Bard-Parker knife. The tissue was then laid back in position.
Surgicel with antibiotic ointment was placed in each nostril and sutured outside the nose with 3-0 nylon.
Surgicel with antibiotic ointment was placed in each nostril and sutured outside the nose with 3-0 nylon.
The patient was then awakened and taken to recovery room in good condition.
